We start by gathering the given facts:
• Harold is Doris’s ancestor.
• David is Jean’s ancestor.
• Edward is David’s ancestor.

Tracing the lineages, we see:
– Harold is placed higher than Doris.
– On a separate chain, Edward is an ancestor of David, who in turn is an ancestor of Jean.

There is no fact connecting any person in Harold’s chain (Harold → … → Doris) with any person in Jean’s chain (Edward → David → Jean). Hence, no relationship (ancestor, descendant, common ancestor, or common descendant) between Harold and Jean can be deduced from the given information.

Thus, the correct answer is that none of the provided options apply.

<ANSWER>5</ANSWER>
